WEBVTT

1
00:00:39.122 --> 00:00:40.331
Jesus Christ.

2
00:00:42.292 --> 00:00:44.794
Kid! It's Frank.

3
00:00:46.504 --> 00:00:48.465
Frank. Frank.

4
00:00:49.299 --> 00:00:52.260
- Frank. she wants to arrest you.
Just give me the gun. kid.

5
00:00:52.886 --> 00:00:54.345
She's gonna sell you out.

6
00:00:55.055 --> 00:00:56.056
Hey...

7
00:00:56.681 --> 00:00:57.807
give me the gun.

8
00:00:59.225 --> 00:01:00.351
It's okay.

9
00:01:01.644 --> 00:01:02.854
It's okay. kid.

10
00:01:16.034 --> 00:01:17.243
Where the hell were you?

11
00:01:19.788 --> 00:01:21.289
Went to get some advice.

12
00:01:22.832 --> 00:01:24.209
Yeah? By who?

13
00:01:31.257 --> 00:01:32.258
My wife.

14
00:01:33.843 --> 00:01:36.054
Well. did she tell you
how out of line you were?

15
00:01:48.983 --> 00:01:50.819
Are you really here to take me in?

16
00:01:52.070 --> 00:01:54.697
Or you just didn't have
any other place to go?

17
00:01:55.532 --> 00:01:58.118
Yeah. her and everybody else. Frank.

18
00:01:59.077 --> 00:02:00.453
And whose fault is that?

19
00:02:01.246 --> 00:02:04.665
Nobody likes making their Friday night
the Punisher pity party.

20
00:02:04.666 --> 00:02:05.875
you know what I mean?

21
00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:21.431
If you had asked me once.

22
00:02:21.432 --> 00:02:24.477
I would've told you
I was pretty much just like anyone else.

23
00:02:27.313 --> 00:02:31.776
And all I really gave a shit about
was that my family was healthy or happy.

24
00:02:34.654 --> 00:02:35.780
But I lost them.

25
00:02:37.365 --> 00:02:38.658
Everything changed.

26
00:02:39.951 --> 00:02:43.872
I thought I became something different.

27
00:02:48.251 --> 00:02:49.502
But last night.

28
00:02:50.879 --> 00:02:52.672
I had a little chat with my wife.

29
00:02:55.466 --> 00:02:58.052
I sat by her grave.
and I realized something.

30
00:03:00.722 --> 00:03:02.348
This is always who I was.

31
00:03:06.311 --> 00:03:07.437
And Maria...

32
00:03:09.439 --> 00:03:10.523
she knew.

33
00:03:12.901 --> 00:03:14.235
She knew what I was.

34
00:03:16.070 --> 00:03:17.405
She loved me anyway.

35
00:03:26.831 --> 00:03:27.832
I'm just...

36
00:03:29.334 --> 00:03:30.877
I'm not like you people.

37
00:03:31.628 --> 00:03:33.630
You know. I can do things you can't do.

38
00:03:36.799 --> 00:03:38.092
Whatever that makes me...

39
00:03:40.970 --> 00:03:41.971
it makes me.

40
00:03:51.773 --> 00:03:52.773
This.

41
00:03:52.774 --> 00:03:55.151
It has to end. Frank.

42
00:03:56.027 --> 00:03:57.487
Who's gonna end it. though?

43
00:03:58.780 --> 00:03:59.781
You?

44
00:04:01.449 --> 00:04:02.492
Mahoney?

45
00:04:04.661 --> 00:04:06.036
You take Bill to jail.

46
00:04:06.037 --> 00:04:08.581
this billionaire asshole
is coming after her.

47
00:04:11.793 --> 00:04:15.545
These people. they won't stop.
They can't stop.

48
00:04:15.546 --> 00:04:17.382
They don't give a shit about your law.

49
00:04:20.093 --> 00:04:22.636
So what the hell am I doing
carrying this badge?

50
00:04:22.637 --> 00:04:23.721
Yeah.

51
00:04:27.642 --> 00:04:29.227
I can't answer that for you.

52
00:04:30.895 --> 00:04:33.273
I don't have answers for any of you.

53
00:04:34.607 --> 00:04:36.317
Then what are you asking?

54
00:04:38.695 --> 00:04:40.780
Let me be what I'm meant to be.

55
00:06:07.033 --> 00:06:09.452
<i>Serpent Five.
this is Serpent Six. We are go for launch.</i>

56
00:06:12.455 --> 00:06:15.957
<i>Serpent Six. this is Serpent Five.
We are waiting at the door.</i>

57
00:06:15.958 --> 00:06:17.794
<i>Copy. Serpent Five.
you're a go for action.</i>

58
00:06:31.182 --> 00:06:33.309
<i>Copy. Serpent Five. you're a go for entry.</i>

59
00:06:40.566 --> 00:06:42.402
<i>You know this can't last forever.</i>

60
00:06:43.569 --> 00:06:44.779
<i>You're too smart not to.</i>

61
00:06:48.324 --> 00:06:49.325
Okay.

62
00:06:50.451 --> 00:06:52.912
But that doesn't mean we can't make plans.

63
00:06:54.372 --> 00:06:55.415
For after.

64
00:06:58.126 --> 00:07:01.629
At some point. enough's got to be enough.

65
00:07:02.797 --> 00:07:04.799
It all has to be for something.

66
00:07:09.303 --> 00:07:10.138
It will.

67
00:07:10.139 --> 00:07:11.721
<i>Police say four people are dead</i>

68
00:07:11.722 --> 00:07:12.682
<i>and three wounded</i>

69
00:07:12.683 --> 00:07:14.224
<i>in a gang-related gun battle</i>

70
00:07:14.225 --> 00:07:16.977
<i>that broke out
in a Lower East Side housing project.</i>

71
00:07:16.978 --> 00:07:19.980
<i>Some are calling it
the major salvo in a gang war.</i>

72
00:07:19.981 --> 00:07:23.359
<i>one of at least three such raids
in the last 24 hours.</i>

73
00:07:24.318 --> 00:07:26.195
With the money. we can go anywhere...

74
00:07:28.990 --> 00:07:32.243
be anything we want to be. Together.

75
00:07:35.913 --> 00:07:36.998
And we will.

76
00:07:38.958 --> 00:07:40.042
I promise.

77
00:07:46.215 --> 00:07:48.341
But you have to let me
deal with Frank first.

78
00:07:48.342 --> 00:07:50.927
<i>It has been a violent and bloody 24 hours</i>

79
00:07:50.928 --> 00:07:52.304
<i>here in the New York area...</i>

80
00:07:52.305 --> 00:07:53.680
<i>as three separate...</i>

81
00:07:53.681 --> 00:07:55.474
<i>Gang activity is on the rise in New York.</i>

82
00:07:55.475 --> 00:07:57.642
<i>- as multiple fatalities... A bizarre scene.</i>

83
00:07:57.643 --> 00:08:00.855
<i>witnesses report seeing a gang
in frightening masks.</i>

84
00:08:01.439 --> 00:08:02.356
Fellas.

85
00:08:07.487 --> 00:08:08.321
Two months.

86
00:08:08.322 --> 00:08:10.071
<i>According to police. the men in masks</i>

87
00:08:10.072 --> 00:08:11.698
<i>gunned down everyone inside the building</i>

88
00:08:11.699 --> 00:08:14.159
<i>and made off with nearly
a half million dollars in contraband.</i>

89
00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:16.912
<i>...making off with more
than half a million dollars in cash.</i>

90
00:08:16.913 --> 00:08:18.331
<i>drugs and weapons.</i>

91
00:08:24.462 --> 00:08:26.797
Don't let Frank define who you are.

92
00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:30.426
Look at me.

93
00:08:35.389 --> 00:08:36.432
Really look.

94
00:08:40.853 --> 00:08:42.897
I have to know why he wants me dead.

95
00:08:46.025 --> 00:08:47.568
I have to know.

96
00:09:06.879 --> 00:09:09.298
- No. I'm good.

97
00:09:10.466 --> 00:09:12.926
Hey. come on. Sit down.
It's not a big deal.

98
00:09:12.927 --> 00:09:15.971
- Dude! Get... get off of me!
- I'm testing the merchandise.

99
00:09:15.972 --> 00:09:18.306
I'm not merchandise. asshole!
Get your hands off of me.

100
00:09:18.307 --> 00:09:19.474
Listen. bitch...

101
00:09:19.475 --> 00:09:20.560
Moke!

102
00:09:23.729 --> 00:09:25.439
Play nice with our guests.

103
00:09:38.286 --> 00:09:41.121
This new driver is supposed to get me
an extra ten yards.

104
00:09:41.122 --> 00:09:43.833
So far. it's not the game changer
I thought it would be.

105
00:09:44.792 --> 00:09:47.503
Perhaps I'm misplacing my faith.

106
00:09:50.798 --> 00:09:53.883
The scrutiny Castle is under worries me.

107
00:09:53.884 --> 00:09:58.598
If the police apprehend him or the girl.
they may try to leverage what they have.

108
00:10:00.266 --> 00:10:01.475
And what is that?

109
00:10:02.685 --> 00:10:04.228
Do you have faith in me. John?

110
00:10:06.188 --> 00:10:07.189
I do.

111
00:10:10.943 --> 00:10:12.737
Well. these are testing times.

112
00:10:14.572 --> 00:10:17.199
I think we need to take radical steps.

113
00:10:18.701 --> 00:10:21.787
I want you to use your old contacts
here in the city.

114
00:10:22.997 --> 00:10:25.416
Set a bounty on Castle and the girl.

115
00:10:26.626 --> 00:10:28.377
Turn this city against them.

116
00:10:29.337 --> 00:10:31.421
It's better that I do it myself.

117
00:10:31.422 --> 00:10:34.758
It's good that you have
such faith in yourself. as do I.

118
00:10:34.759 --> 00:10:37.845
but we cannot afford pride at this moment.

119
00:10:41.390 --> 00:10:43.975
Castle shot up a city street
in broad daylight.

120
00:10:43.976 --> 00:10:47.480
We're way past the time
for keeping things quiet.

121
00:10:48.481 --> 00:10:50.608
It's risky. me opening old doors.

122
00:10:51.776 --> 00:10:53.694
You're not the man you were.

123
00:10:55.363 --> 00:10:57.782
John. I just want to get ya home.

124
00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:02.577
Rebecca's fortitude is a wonder.
Her spirit is so strong.

125
00:11:02.578 --> 00:11:08.000
And they put on a great face
when you're not there. your boys.

126
00:11:09.752 --> 00:11:13.213
No one knows
how much our families need us.

127
00:11:13.214 --> 00:11:14.465
Any of us.

128
00:11:15.091 --> 00:11:18.886
All the things we do for them
that they can never know.

129
00:11:20.304 --> 00:11:22.598
You'll be home soon. God willing.

130
00:11:23.724 --> 00:11:25.184
Yes. God willing.

131
00:11:27.603 --> 00:11:28.854
Now let's finish it.

132
00:11:30.773 --> 00:11:32.233
Let's get ya home.

133
00:11:35.945 --> 00:11:37.654
<i>...Six. this is Kingdom Five.</i>

134
00:11:37.655 --> 00:11:39.698
<i>We're northbound
on the Phase Line Jupiter.</i>

135
00:11:39.699 --> 00:11:41.366
<i>Two clicks out from OBJ Zebra.</i>

136
00:11:41.367 --> 00:11:43.494
They're staying within a certain area.

137
00:11:44.412 --> 00:11:47.456
Yeah. it's probably a radius
from wherever they're based.

138
00:11:48.207 --> 00:11:50.083
<i>Kingdom Five. this is Kingdom Six.</i>

139
00:11:50.084 --> 00:11:52.168
<i>we are Molotov at this time.</i>

140
00:11:52.169 --> 00:11:53.294
What's Molotov?

141
00:11:53.295 --> 00:11:56.589
We use certain words
to indicate operational steps.

142
00:11:56.590 --> 00:11:58.843
Molotov means they're in position
with their target.

143
00:12:02.430 --> 00:12:03.514
Hey. Curt.

144
00:12:08.936 --> 00:12:11.188
Okay. Yeah. I'm on the move.

145
00:12:24.326 --> 00:12:25.327
Let's go! Let's go!

146
00:12:32.960 --> 00:12:33.961
Shit.

147
00:13:17.087 --> 00:13:21.674
Well. now I know
why we don't see you home so much.

148
00:13:21.675 --> 00:13:24.094
We do have golf courses there.
too. you know?

149
00:13:26.013 --> 00:13:29.098
Your mother often wonders
if you came to New York for the job.

150
00:13:29.099 --> 00:13:31.059
or you took the job for New York.

151
00:13:31.060 --> 00:13:32.144
Both.

152
00:13:35.147 --> 00:13:36.398
God damn it!

153
00:13:38.442 --> 00:13:39.527
Now. now. Dad.

154
00:13:40.277 --> 00:13:43.572
What would the faithful think
if they were to hear you blaspheming?

155
00:13:44.156 --> 00:13:47.033
Well. son. you see.
there's two kinds of blasphemy.

156
00:13:47.034 --> 00:13:51.121
There's the ones that people
are happy to forgive. and...

157
00:13:52.331 --> 00:13:53.916
then there's the stuff that they aren't.

158
00:13:55.167 --> 00:13:56.335
Here we go.

159
00:13:57.294 --> 00:13:59.046
I think people might surprise you.

160
00:13:59.713 --> 00:14:00.797
Times have changed.

161
00:14:00.798 --> 00:14:03.049
Yeah. not that much. and you know it.

162
00:14:03.050 --> 00:14:04.300
I don't like surprises.

163
00:14:04.301 --> 00:14:06.803
Surprises mean you haven't prepared.
I like to be prepared.

164
00:14:06.804 --> 00:14:08.596
What you like is to be in control.

165
00:14:08.597 --> 00:14:09.598
Yes.

166
00:14:13.185 --> 00:14:14.311
Very nice.

167
00:14:15.229 --> 00:14:18.273
I'm just wondering why the visit?

168
00:14:18.274 --> 00:14:21.986
Unless it's to nag me
about finding a wife for party optics.

169
00:14:23.195 --> 00:14:26.155
When was the last time
we had a conversation about my life

170
00:14:26.156 --> 00:14:28.616
that didn't sound like campaign strategy?

171
00:14:28.617 --> 00:14:32.412
When was the last time
you just asked me if I was happy?

172
00:14:32.413 --> 00:14:35.165
Happy? What the hell is happy?

173
00:14:37.126 --> 00:14:40.546
Son. we are in a position
to change this country for the better.

174
00:14:41.255 --> 00:14:44.632
People take a look at you. and they see
an example they want to follow.

175
00:14:44.633 --> 00:14:49.096
People want to believe. David.
in something.

176
00:14:50.097 --> 00:14:52.766
Because it's a terrifying world
to be alone.

177
00:14:53.809 --> 00:14:55.477
So they need faith.

178
00:14:56.145 --> 00:14:58.897
They take a look at me.
they see all that I've achieved.

179
00:14:58.898 --> 00:15:00.441
and it makes sense.

180
00:15:01.483 --> 00:15:06.572
How could I have all of this
if God hadn't chosen it for me?

181
00:15:08.908 --> 00:15:11.160
It's a question I ask myself every day.

182
00:15:12.119 --> 00:15:15.664
We are living proof that faith is rewarded.

183
00:15:24.423 --> 00:15:25.341
See?

184
00:15:26.800 --> 00:15:30.054
David. I want you to come home
for a little while.

185
00:15:30.971 --> 00:15:34.183
Talk to some people. Donors. Press flesh.

186
00:15:35.309 --> 00:15:37.186
Just a couple of weeks. that's all.

187
00:15:38.395 --> 00:15:40.356
Just to get some things out of the way.

188
00:15:41.565 --> 00:15:43.651
What is so important right now?

189
00:15:52.451 --> 00:15:53.452
Yeah?

190
00:16:02.962 --> 00:16:04.004
Nice suit.

191
00:16:06.340 --> 00:16:07.633
I heard about you.

192
00:16:08.467 --> 00:16:10.469
The man with the five million. am I right?

193
00:16:11.929 --> 00:16:14.139
I'm kind of insulted
you didn't come here first.

194
00:16:14.932 --> 00:16:16.307
Does that mean you don't want to talk?

195
00:16:16.308 --> 00:16:19.519
No. No. Just sayin'. word travels fast.

196
00:16:19.520 --> 00:16:21.814
Would have liked my guys
to have a head start.

197
00:16:32.074 --> 00:16:34.492
I thought this guy was dead already.

198
00:16:34.493 --> 00:16:36.537
Now I know why you're offering so much.

199
00:16:37.538 --> 00:16:39.331
I want Castle and the girl alive.

200
00:16:40.416 --> 00:16:42.584
Tell me where they are
or bring them to me.

201
00:16:44.294 --> 00:16:45.212
How alive?

202
00:16:47.214 --> 00:16:48.841
One of them needs to talk.

203
00:16:54.388 --> 00:16:55.514
Put out the word.

204
00:16:56.557 --> 00:16:58.434
Call me on this if you have anything.

205
00:17:00.227 --> 00:17:02.521
Hey. Where are you from?

206
00:17:03.856 --> 00:17:05.565
You don't seem
like you're from around here.

207
00:17:05.566 --> 00:17:06.900
don't mind me saying.

208
00:17:20.372 --> 00:17:21.790
Hey. it's Danny. Put him on.

209
00:17:22.958 --> 00:17:25.002
He's gonna want to hear
what I have to say. trust me.

210
00:17:25.627 --> 00:17:26.879
<i>What is it?</i>

211
00:17:27.629 --> 00:17:29.590
Guess who just walked into my place.

212
00:17:31.759 --> 00:17:33.302
A goddamn ghost.

213
00:17:39.808 --> 00:17:40.808
Thanks.

214
00:17:40.809 --> 00:17:43.145
Yeah. Living the dream.

215
00:17:49.693 --> 00:17:52.863
Would you still be in the military
if you didn't lose your leg?

216
00:17:54.573 --> 00:17:56.158
No. I'd be getting too old.

217
00:17:57.076 --> 00:18:00.036
You see. that's the thing.
is when you sign up.

218
00:18:00.037 --> 00:18:02.830
it never enters your mind
that it isn't forever.

219
00:18:02.831 --> 00:18:07.544
Just some young kid full of ideas
of travel. adventure and war.

220
00:18:09.379 --> 00:18:12.174
Unless you're an officer.
there's always a second life.

221
00:18:13.175 --> 00:18:14.343
Now what about you?

222
00:18:15.177 --> 00:18:17.095
Is this how you saw yourself?

223
00:18:17.096 --> 00:18:20.807
Yeah. I love mobile living.

224
00:18:20.808 --> 00:18:22.559
My fold-out life.

225
00:18:25.479 --> 00:18:29.232
It seems like your chosen line of work
is pretty damn sketchy.

226
00:18:29.233 --> 00:18:30.984
even before Frank turned up.

227
00:18:31.860 --> 00:18:37.740
Shouldn't you be somewhere? Home?
Freaking your old man out about boys?

228
00:18:37.741 --> 00:18:39.201
Learning how to drive?

229
00:18:42.746 --> 00:18:43.789
Marine salvage.

230
00:18:45.207 --> 00:18:46.207
Say what?

231
00:18:46.208 --> 00:18:47.376
Marine salvage.

232
00:18:48.627 --> 00:18:50.212
That's what I've always wanted to do.

233
00:18:50.754 --> 00:18:52.381
I saw a documentary on it once.

234
00:18:53.173 --> 00:18:56.885
Find treasure under the sea.
And if you find it. you get to keep it.

235
00:18:58.011 --> 00:19:00.012
You know what. Amy?
Just forget I even asked.

236
00:19:00.013 --> 00:19:02.141
No. No. seriously.

237
00:19:03.725 --> 00:19:05.643
I remember they were in the Caribbean.

238
00:19:05.644 --> 00:19:10.983
and the sea was so green
and there was all this sun.

239
00:19:11.817 --> 00:19:14.486
And there was no noise under the water.

240
00:19:15.028 --> 00:19:18.031
Just all this old stuff
waiting to be found. Like...

241
00:19:18.699 --> 00:19:21.326
Spanish gold and jewels and stuff.

242
00:19:22.077 --> 00:19:22.911
Hmm.

243
00:19:24.246 --> 00:19:27.916
I guess if we get out from under.
there's no stopping you from going. huh?

244
00:19:28.959 --> 00:19:32.004
Shit like this definitely makes you
reassess your goals.

245
00:19:35.007 --> 00:19:36.215
I can't even swim.

246
00:19:36.216 --> 00:19:40.971
Actually. I've never seen the ocean.
So... there's that.

247
00:19:45.475 --> 00:19:48.353
He could at least call
and let us know what the hell is going on.

248
00:19:49.146 --> 00:19:50.272
Frank?

249
00:19:51.023 --> 00:19:52.356
Yeah. right.

250
00:19:52.357 --> 00:19:55.610
Come on. Curtis. He's selfish.

251
00:19:55.611 --> 00:19:58.905
He says all of this is for us. but it's not.

252
00:19:58.906 --> 00:20:00.781
He's got an itch.
and he's gonna scratch it.

253
00:20:00.782 --> 00:20:03.202
We're just. like. the staff.

254
00:20:05.245 --> 00:20:06.704
You know what? You're right.

255
00:20:06.705 --> 00:20:10.209
Yeah. I usually am. It's kind of a gift.

256
00:20:11.752 --> 00:20:14.670
Look. I got someplace I need to be.

257
00:20:14.671 --> 00:20:17.840
I'm letting some people down.
And they get let down a lot.

258
00:20:17.841 --> 00:20:20.718
Frank is out doing his own thing.
and I'mma do mine.

259
00:20:20.719 --> 00:20:23.346
So. what? You're just gonna leave me here?

260
00:20:23.347 --> 00:20:26.849
I don't get to have a thing?
My thing is just sitting around waiting?

261
00:20:26.850 --> 00:20:28.309
Like a dog nobody wants.

262
00:20:28.310 --> 00:20:31.897
- You're gonna be safe here.
- No. I'm not. I'm just alone.

263
00:20:32.648 --> 00:20:35.024
I could be doing this literally anywhere.

264
00:20:35.025 --> 00:20:38.820
Anywhere with. like. clean sheets
and a properly-flushing bathroom.

265
00:20:39.738 --> 00:20:41.739
Come on. take me with you. Curtis.

266
00:20:41.740 --> 00:20:43.575
I can't.
- Yeah. you can.

267
00:20:45.619 --> 00:20:48.413
Well... then. I won't.

268
00:22:40.942 --> 00:22:42.194
What will it be?

269
00:22:44.154 --> 00:22:45.780
You can help me out.

270
00:22:45.781 --> 00:22:49.325
There's a group of vets
running around town causing trouble.

271
00:22:49.326 --> 00:22:51.035
I hear maybe you've been
partying with them.

272
00:22:51.036 --> 00:22:52.913
- No idea what you're talking about.
- No?

273
00:22:54.122 --> 00:22:56.083
Okay. Well...

274
00:22:57.667 --> 00:22:58.960
Maybe this will help you.

275
00:23:07.427 --> 00:23:08.428
Who's that?

276
00:23:09.513 --> 00:23:11.139
I don't want any trouble.

277
00:23:12.516 --> 00:23:13.642
Where are they?

278
00:23:17.145 --> 00:23:19.773
If I talk. do you promise
none of this comes back on me?

279
00:23:20.607 --> 00:23:22.025
You're not my problem.

280
00:23:23.527 --> 00:23:24.944
Shit. what do I care?

281
00:23:24.945 --> 00:23:27.154
Those guys were total assholes.

282
00:23:27.155 --> 00:23:28.697
Especially him.

283
00:23:28.698 --> 00:23:30.951
Cut anything else off him.
that'd make my day.

284
00:23:32.494 --> 00:23:35.496
They call it Valhalla.

285
00:23:35.497 --> 00:23:38.165
I don't know.
some Viking bullshit or something.

286
00:23:38.166 --> 00:23:39.834
They're off the rails.

287
00:23:39.835 --> 00:23:41.920
Stealing shit. partying all night.

288
00:23:43.505 --> 00:23:44.923
Tony knows some of them.

289
00:23:45.465 --> 00:23:48.051
Sounded like it could be fun.
so I went along.

290
00:23:48.718 --> 00:23:50.470
Turned out it wasn't so much.

291
00:23:51.054 --> 00:23:53.348
Frat house bullshit turned up to 11.

292
00:23:55.058 --> 00:23:56.600
You know where?

293
00:23:56.601 --> 00:23:58.227
Somewhere in Queens.

294
00:23:58.228 --> 00:23:59.770
It was dark. I don't know.

295
00:23:59.771 --> 00:24:02.106
A warehouse. Maybe north of 14th.
Something like that.

296
00:24:02.107 --> 00:24:03.525
Okay.

297
00:24:07.404 --> 00:24:08.572
Appreciate it.

298
00:24:12.534 --> 00:24:13.577
Hey. Tony.

299
00:24:15.454 --> 00:24:16.746
Call it a tip.

300
00:24:38.768 --> 00:24:40.270
You assholes lost?

301
00:24:45.484 --> 00:24:48.028
Yeah. we were looking for $5 million.

302
00:24:48.612 --> 00:24:50.947
And it was stupid enough
to show up on its own.

303
00:24:51.823 --> 00:24:53.365
What are you talking about?

304
00:24:53.366 --> 00:24:55.576
Someone's had enough
of your shit. Castle.

305
00:24:55.577 --> 00:24:57.120
Put a bounty on your head.

306
00:24:58.163 --> 00:24:59.830
- Where's the girl?
- What girl?

307
00:24:59.831 --> 00:25:01.665
Someone wants you and some kid.

308
00:25:01.666 --> 00:25:03.584
You're gonna take us to her.

309
00:25:03.585 --> 00:25:04.794
Who are they?

310
00:25:05.921 --> 00:25:10.675
Listen. asshole.
there's one of you. and six...

311
00:25:23.688 --> 00:25:24.689
Let's talk.

312
00:26:15.740 --> 00:26:16.825
Tough day?

313
00:26:36.761 --> 00:26:38.972
They did a hell of a job fixing your face.

314
00:26:41.099 --> 00:26:42.142
Considering.

315
00:26:44.185 --> 00:26:45.394
You sound disappointed.

316
00:26:45.395 --> 00:26:47.021
- I am.
- Were you there?

317
00:26:47.022 --> 00:26:50.191
What does your file say?
Your lawyer must have read it to you.

318
00:26:55.322 --> 00:26:57.657
It says that you arrested me.

319
00:27:00.827 --> 00:27:02.537
But that I shot you.

320
00:27:05.373 --> 00:27:06.916
I don't remember any of that.

321
00:27:08.627 --> 00:27:11.421
It also says that we were together.
me and you.

322
00:27:12.631 --> 00:27:14.174
I'd hardly call it that.

323
00:27:15.967 --> 00:27:17.844
Then why do you hate me so much?

324
00:27:19.554 --> 00:27:21.765
You really don't know. do you?

325
00:27:22.682 --> 00:27:24.059
All those nights...

326
00:27:25.852 --> 00:27:27.228
all those mornings...

327
00:27:28.063 --> 00:27:29.064
wasted.

328
00:27:29.731 --> 00:27:31.024
A year of your life.

329
00:27:33.360 --> 00:27:34.444
That's...

330
00:27:35.028 --> 00:27:36.446
some kind of commitment.

331
00:27:37.781 --> 00:27:38.782
I...

332
00:27:39.449 --> 00:27:40.450
I envy you.

333
00:27:41.201 --> 00:27:42.911
I envy you remembering. I...

334
00:27:45.038 --> 00:27:46.538
envy you knowing how you feel.

335
00:27:46.539 --> 00:27:49.793
I should know how I felt about you.

336
00:27:56.966 --> 00:27:59.094
I mean. did we...

337
00:28:02.722 --> 00:28:04.056
Here. in this place?

338
00:28:04.057 --> 00:28:05.266
Why are you here?

339
00:28:08.186 --> 00:28:09.187
Answers.

340
00:28:14.401 --> 00:28:16.403
Okay. can I make another drink at least?

341
00:28:18.446 --> 00:28:19.781
Knock yourself out.

342
00:28:21.116 --> 00:28:22.158
You want one?

343
00:28:24.452 --> 00:28:27.996
Hey. if that backup gun were still
in there. would you try to shoot me?

344
00:28:27.997 --> 00:28:29.416
In a heartbeat.

345
00:28:30.250 --> 00:28:33.627
Guess you're in charge. Billy. In control.
Just how you've always liked it.

346
00:28:33.628 --> 00:28:36.381
You know. you might not remember.
but you haven't changed.

347
00:28:37.090 --> 00:28:40.259
Same psychotic asshole you always were.

348
00:28:40.260 --> 00:28:43.137
Yeah. I can see why I liked you.

349
00:28:43.138 --> 00:28:44.973
- You used me.
- Maybe.

350
00:28:46.224 --> 00:28:48.059
Doesn't mean I didn't like you. too.

351
00:28:55.984 --> 00:28:58.236
Frank did this to me...

352
00:29:02.574 --> 00:29:03.575
didn't he?

353
00:29:05.452 --> 00:29:06.453
Sorry. who?

354
00:29:07.036 --> 00:29:10.622
No. no. no. no. You don't do that.
You don't do that!

355
00:29:10.623 --> 00:29:12.292
'Cause I know! I know now!

356
00:29:14.210 --> 00:29:15.753
Nobody...

357
00:29:15.754 --> 00:29:18.590
nobody seems to have the answers.
But you do. I know you do.

358
00:29:19.966 --> 00:29:23.178
So I need to know how.

359
00:29:36.900 --> 00:29:39.568
You sold out
everything you ever stood for.

360
00:29:39.569 --> 00:29:43.530
anyone you ever cared about.
and you did it for money and status.

361
00:29:43.531 --> 00:29:46.909
Left Frank for dead. covered in the blood
of his wife and children.

362
00:29:46.910 --> 00:29:48.952
- That's who you are.
- No. No...

363
00:29:48.953 --> 00:29:52.081
Yeah. And when he found out.
he came after you and he made you pay.

364
00:29:54.793 --> 00:29:57.002
Now. look me in the eye
and tell me something.

365
00:29:57.003 --> 00:29:58.129
Am I lying?

366
00:30:03.259 --> 00:30:07.179
Frank wanted you to live with it
on your face every day.

367
00:30:07.180 --> 00:30:10.683
He put all that ugly on the outside
where it belongs.

368
00:30:12.560 --> 00:30:16.189
And maybe you should just
do us all a favor and shoot yourself.

369
00:30:16.731 --> 00:30:18.149
Get it over with.

370
00:30:19.400 --> 00:30:22.153
Because Frank will come after you. and...

371
00:30:23.488 --> 00:30:25.573
he will finish the job.

372
00:30:33.581 --> 00:30:36.084
I'm a hard man to kill. Agent Madani.

373
00:30:42.048 --> 00:30:44.384
Did we have some good times. Dinah?

374
00:30:46.261 --> 00:30:47.554
I'll bet we did.

375
00:30:50.974 --> 00:30:51.975
Yeah.

376
00:30:53.101 --> 00:30:55.645
Look at how much
you want to kill me right now.

377
00:30:57.272 --> 00:30:58.481
We definitely did.

378
00:31:00.441 --> 00:31:02.735
I dreamed about Frank every night.

379
00:31:05.321 --> 00:31:06.906
Who did you dream about?

380
00:31:10.785 --> 00:31:11.870
But. hey...

381
00:31:13.371 --> 00:31:15.623
at least you will
always have the memories.

382
00:31:16.666 --> 00:31:17.709
Am I right?

383
00:31:20.795 --> 00:31:21.796
Right.

384
00:31:24.299 --> 00:31:26.134
I'll leave your weapons downstairs.

385
00:31:28.261 --> 00:31:30.053
If you try to follow me.

386
00:31:30.054 --> 00:31:32.098
my men outside in the hallway
will kill you.

387
00:32:16.935 --> 00:32:18.101
<i>Who is it?</i>

388
00:32:18.102 --> 00:32:19.187
It's me.

389
00:32:20.229 --> 00:32:21.230
It's Amy.

390
00:32:29.697 --> 00:32:31.866
Shan! Hey.
- Amy.

391
00:32:33.076 --> 00:32:34.410
- Hey. Hi.

392
00:32:35.745 --> 00:32:36.579
Um...

393
00:32:37.538 --> 00:32:40.791
Yeah. this is my friend's place. actually.

394
00:32:40.792 --> 00:32:44.671
I'm just staying here
while my apartment gets renovated. so...

395
00:32:45.213 --> 00:32:50.550
Well. I have been living in a trailer
with a backed-up toilet. so...

396
00:32:50.551 --> 00:32:54.638
Hey. at least it's not
that place that Fiona had us living in.

397
00:32:54.639 --> 00:32:56.515
What was that place
above the Indian restaurant

398
00:32:56.516 --> 00:32:57.683
with all the mice?

399
00:32:57.684 --> 00:32:59.477
Oh! I totally forgot about that.

400
00:33:00.353 --> 00:33:02.814
Yeah. You're not with Fiona anymore?

401
00:33:03.398 --> 00:33:05.566
I didn't think you'd be the one to take off.

402
00:33:07.068 --> 00:33:08.069
She's dead.

403
00:33:09.612 --> 00:33:11.114
They all are. actually.

404
00:33:12.031 --> 00:33:13.783
Oh! Shit.

405
00:33:14.575 --> 00:33:16.786
That's heavy. What happened?

406
00:33:17.870 --> 00:33:19.288
You know. honestly...

407
00:33:20.248 --> 00:33:22.500
it's probably better if I just don't tell you.

408
00:33:23.042 --> 00:33:24.209
Seriously.

409
00:33:24.210 --> 00:33:26.546
Look. I just... I gotta disappear.

410
00:33:27.088 --> 00:33:29.132
You told me you were
connected up here. yeah?

411
00:33:29.716 --> 00:33:31.300
You think you could hook me up?

412
00:33:32.301 --> 00:33:34.512
Sure. Yeah. I got a guy.

413
00:33:35.054 --> 00:33:39.392
But it's not free.
And if you want it fast. it'll be more.

414
00:33:49.277 --> 00:33:51.862
- That all you got?
- Don't hustle me. Shan.

415
00:33:51.863 --> 00:33:53.531
Force of habit.

416
00:33:56.743 --> 00:33:57.744
Who's that?

417
00:33:58.870 --> 00:33:59.871
Uh...

418
00:34:00.413 --> 00:34:01.706
No one important.

419
00:34:05.835 --> 00:34:08.336
Go make yourself comfortable.
I'll make some calls.

420
00:34:08.337 --> 00:34:09.422
Thanks.

421
00:34:54.550 --> 00:34:56.760
Man. what you did to Jake wasn't cool.

422
00:34:56.761 --> 00:34:58.429
You ever known me to miss a meeting?

423
00:34:59.931 --> 00:35:02.265
Not be there when any of you guys called?

424
00:35:02.266 --> 00:35:04.227
Share a secret that you've shared?

425
00:35:04.769 --> 00:35:06.020
No.

426
00:35:06.687 --> 00:35:07.814
I got you.

427
00:35:08.981 --> 00:35:10.066
And you know why?

428
00:35:10.817 --> 00:35:12.568
Because of what we shared.

429
00:35:13.194 --> 00:35:15.613
Because of what we have in common.

430
00:35:16.906 --> 00:35:20.910
Because we know what it means
to have someone you can put your faith in.

431
00:35:22.411 --> 00:35:25.164
And the problem with faith
is that people abuse it.

432
00:35:26.165 --> 00:35:29.127
Jake was running with Billy Russo.

433
00:35:29.752 --> 00:35:31.837
Yeah. the same asshole that shot me

434
00:35:31.838 --> 00:35:35.173
is running around shooting up shit.
robbing and murdering.

435
00:35:35.174 --> 00:35:37.425
and recruiting guys like us
to help him do it.

436
00:35:37.426 --> 00:35:41.222
I called you because I had faith
that you'd be no part of it.

437
00:35:42.223 --> 00:35:44.307
The fact that I'm still
standing here breathing

438
00:35:44.308 --> 00:35:46.226
means that I got that right.

439
00:35:46.227 --> 00:35:47.562
Yeah. you did.

440
00:35:48.104 --> 00:35:49.729
So you want us to fight your fight?

441
00:35:49.730 --> 00:35:52.733
No. no. I just want you to find him.

442
00:35:53.359 --> 00:35:57.321
We'll find 'em. Some of those assholes
ain't exactly quiet about their shit.

443
00:36:02.743 --> 00:36:03.744
Kid!

444
00:36:17.175 --> 00:36:18.176
God damn it.

445
00:36:23.556 --> 00:36:24.681
Yeah?

446
00:36:24.682 --> 00:36:27.100
<i>Hey. Where are you?</i>

447
00:36:27.101 --> 00:36:28.643
<i>Yeah. I told you to stay put.</i>

448
00:36:28.644 --> 00:36:30.604
<i>You were gonna listen to the radio.
We had a plan.</i>

449
00:36:30.605 --> 00:36:33.815
Yeah. what Billy's doing is affecting
more people than just us.

450
00:36:33.816 --> 00:36:35.108
If he's recruiting vets.

451
00:36:35.109 --> 00:36:36.902
then my guys should be able
to find out where they are.

452
00:36:36.903 --> 00:36:39.196
Hey. Curt. look.
I know where he is. all right?

453
00:36:39.197 --> 00:36:42.200
It's a warehouse in Queens.
The kid's with you. right?

454
00:36:43.618 --> 00:36:45.327
No. she was there when I left.

455
00:36:45.328 --> 00:36:46.412
God...

456
00:36:47.663 --> 00:36:49.372
What did I say to you. Curtis?

457
00:36:49.373 --> 00:36:51.583
What did I say to you?
You were supposed to watch her.

458
00:36:51.584 --> 00:36:53.752
- Look. don't start. man. I'm not some...
<i>No. you listen.</i>

459
00:36:53.753 --> 00:36:58.131
There's a contract out on us.
$5 million. $5 million. Curtis.

460
00:36:58.132 --> 00:37:00.508
Every asshole in the city
is looking for her right now.

461
00:37:00.509 --> 00:37:01.635
Shit!

462
00:37:01.636 --> 00:37:02.720
Yeah. shit!

463
00:37:03.512 --> 00:37:04.513
Way to go. Curt.

464
00:37:05.056 --> 00:37:06.015
Damn it!

465
00:37:15.399 --> 00:37:16.775
Take a hint. Frank.

466
00:37:16.776 --> 00:37:20.987
Dial a million times and no one picks up.
it usually means they don't want to talk.

467
00:37:20.988 --> 00:37:23.448
- Hey. where are you? <i>With a friend.</i>

468
00:37:23.449 --> 00:37:24.908
A real one.

469
00:37:24.909 --> 00:37:27.202
Kid. you need to come home.

470
00:37:27.203 --> 00:37:29.247
<i>There's a contract out on us.</i>

471
00:37:29.872 --> 00:37:32.540
Every piece of shit in this city
is looking for you right now.

472
00:37:32.541 --> 00:37:34.292
I need you to come back now.

473
00:37:34.293 --> 00:37:37.129
I'm leaving.
like I should've in the beginning.

474
00:37:37.880 --> 00:37:39.047
Okay.

475
00:37:39.048 --> 00:37:40.257
Listen to me.

476
00:37:40.258 --> 00:37:43.302
I will put you on a train myself.
but you need to come back.

477
00:37:43.844 --> 00:37:46.972
Let me ask you a question. How much
do you trust this friend of yours?

478
00:37:46.973 --> 00:37:49.934
Because right now you're the most
valuable thing they've ever seen.

479
00:37:57.316 --> 00:37:58.567
I loved his family.

480
00:38:01.195 --> 00:38:02.738
I loved his family. The...

481
00:38:03.990 --> 00:38:06.951
closest thing I had to one of my own.
So even if I did...

482
00:38:08.411 --> 00:38:10.454
what they say that I did. Even if...

483
00:38:12.623 --> 00:38:14.041
All right...

484
00:38:14.750 --> 00:38:15.751
kill me.

485
00:38:16.919 --> 00:38:18.421
But to leave me like this?

486
00:38:19.880 --> 00:38:21.340
To carve me up.

487
00:38:22.967 --> 00:38:24.801
There is no honor in that.

488
00:38:24.802 --> 00:38:27.763
After everything...
After everything that we went through.

489
00:38:29.390 --> 00:38:30.850
I deserve more.

490
00:38:36.439 --> 00:38:37.773
I deserve more.

491
00:38:39.567 --> 00:38:41.193
How do you know all of this?

492
00:38:43.070 --> 00:38:44.572
I went to Dinah Madani.

493
00:38:48.075 --> 00:38:50.244
And you didn't think to tell me that?

494
00:38:51.662 --> 00:38:53.914
Do you not know how risky that was?

495
00:38:55.041 --> 00:38:56.125
How'd it feel?

496
00:38:57.710 --> 00:38:59.754
- It didn't... You were lovers once.

497
00:39:03.382 --> 00:39:04.383
Not in here.

498
00:39:07.345 --> 00:39:08.429
And not here.

499
00:39:10.473 --> 00:39:11.474
Hey...

500
00:39:13.142 --> 00:39:17.104
there is only person that matters in here.

501
00:39:20.232 --> 00:39:21.275
And Frank.

502
00:39:23.319 --> 00:39:25.112
She was there when he did this.

503
00:39:25.905 --> 00:39:27.573
Then maybe she knows where he is.

504
00:39:31.619 --> 00:39:32.995
He won't stop.

505
00:39:33.913 --> 00:39:35.581
He won't stop coming. I wouldn't.

506
00:39:36.415 --> 00:39:37.833
We can go anywhere.

507
00:39:39.085 --> 00:39:41.712
He can't find you
if he doesn't know where you are.

508
00:39:42.296 --> 00:39:44.382
And then I will always know that I ran.

509
00:39:45.758 --> 00:39:47.342
I would've put...

510
00:39:47.343 --> 00:39:49.303
I would've put him out of his misery.

511
00:39:49.845 --> 00:39:51.847
You have something special. Billy.

512
00:39:53.140 --> 00:39:55.935
You have built yourself up
from nothing. twice.

513
00:39:56.685 --> 00:39:59.104
Fought your way out of hell
more times than you can count.

514
00:39:59.105 --> 00:40:01.481
Frank didn't take things from you.

515
00:40:01.482 --> 00:40:04.109
He gave you... us...

516
00:40:04.110 --> 00:40:05.694
a second chance.

517
00:40:10.783 --> 00:40:14.537
I want him to feel what I felt.

518
00:40:18.791 --> 00:40:22.378
I want him to suffer. I want him to hurt.

519
00:40:37.476 --> 00:40:38.936
<i>I got something for ya.</i>

520
00:40:40.604 --> 00:40:41.604
Do you have them?

521
00:40:41.605 --> 00:40:43.440
<i>I got someone
who knows where they are.</i>

522
00:40:43.441 --> 00:40:45.192
<i>Come by my restaurant. I'll hook you up.</i>

523
00:40:52.700 --> 00:40:53.701
Soon.

524
00:41:18.350 --> 00:41:19.935
Hey. asshole!

525
00:41:20.686 --> 00:41:22.104
What the hell are you doing?

526
00:41:24.648 --> 00:41:26.066
What's it look like. man?

527
00:42:15.074 --> 00:42:17.159
Remember I called you when payday comes.

528
00:42:19.245 --> 00:42:20.371
It's this one.

529
00:42:31.298 --> 00:42:32.299
She's not here.

530
00:42:39.223 --> 00:42:40.557
What...
- There's no one here.

531
00:42:40.558 --> 00:42:42.518
What? No. She was right there!

532
00:42:49.316 --> 00:42:51.192
No way she could've passed us going up.

533
00:42:51.193 --> 00:42:53.654
I'll stay here.
You guys check the other floors.

534
00:43:24.226 --> 00:43:25.518
Must be him.

535
00:43:25.519 --> 00:43:27.021
Go. I'll find the girl.

536
00:43:53.964 --> 00:43:57.301
Come out! Or I'm gonna start
putting bullets through the door.

537
00:44:04.350 --> 00:44:06.809
Please. Please.

538
00:44:06.810 --> 00:44:08.395
Please just let me go. okay?

539
00:44:29.083 --> 00:44:30.249
Kid!

540
00:44:30.250 --> 00:44:31.626
He's not gonna kill you if you let me go.

541
00:44:31.627 --> 00:44:33.503
Come up here. and she's dead! You hear me?

542
00:44:33.504 --> 00:44:35.922
Hey. hey. hey. hey!
You touch her. I'll kill you!

543
00:44:35.923 --> 00:44:37.840
She's dead if you don't back off!

544
00:44:37.841 --> 00:44:40.094
Hey! I'll pull you apart!

545
00:44:44.306 --> 00:44:45.557
You're not gonna...

546
00:44:46.892 --> 00:44:48.185
Kid!

547
00:44:52.815 --> 00:44:54.191
No!

548
00:45:01.031 --> 00:45:02.032
Easy.

549
00:45:02.574 --> 00:45:03.575
Hey. hey. hey.

550
00:45:05.244 --> 00:45:06.745
God!

551
00:45:07.996 --> 00:45:09.163
Oh. God!

552
00:45:09.164 --> 00:45:10.249
Easy. easy.

553
00:45:12.543 --> 00:45:15.754
- I killed him. I killed him.
Give me the gun.

554
00:45:16.839 --> 00:45:18.172
No.

555
00:45:18.173 --> 00:45:20.967
No. you just shot him. okay? Hey. right?

556
00:45:20.968 --> 00:45:22.593
See that? I killed him.

557
00:45:22.594 --> 00:45:24.762
Right? Yeah?

558
00:45:24.763 --> 00:45:27.557
Hey... we need to go. all right?
Where's your stuff?

559
00:45:27.558 --> 00:45:29.351
Gotta get your stuff
and get you outta here. okay?

560
00:45:30.936 --> 00:45:34.148
No. no. no. no. no. Hey. look at me. Hey.

561
00:45:34.732 --> 00:45:36.357
Listen to me. okay?

562
00:45:36.358 --> 00:45:39.278
His blood ain't worth
a single one of your tears.

563
00:45:41.405 --> 00:45:42.531
Look at me.

564
00:45:43.323 --> 00:45:45.367
Take five seconds. yeah?

565
00:45:52.082 --> 00:45:53.792
Yeah? Yeah?

566
00:45:54.501 --> 00:45:55.877
Attagirl.

567
00:45:55.878 --> 00:45:56.962
Let's go.

568
00:46:24.907 --> 00:46:26.866
They... Amy. look. No. see...

569
00:46:26.867 --> 00:46:27.993
Seriously. look.

570
00:46:28.827 --> 00:46:30.870
See? They made me do it.

571
00:46:30.871 --> 00:46:33.080
Amy... come on.

572
00:46:33.081 --> 00:46:34.458
They made me do it. okay?

573
00:46:50.724 --> 00:46:53.185
Thank you for coming. Please come in.

574
00:47:00.484 --> 00:47:02.736
Can I get you something? Water or tea?

575
00:47:03.403 --> 00:47:04.780
Yeah. I'd take a scotch.

576
00:47:06.073 --> 00:47:08.407
Is that your medication of choice.
Agent Madani?

577
00:47:08.408 --> 00:47:10.701
Whoa. Doctor. you called me. remember?

578
00:47:10.702 --> 00:47:12.663
Sorry. that's a force of habit. Please.

579
00:47:26.552 --> 00:47:28.095
I don't know how you live with it.

580
00:47:30.556 --> 00:47:33.641
Not knowing if somebody
that you arrested or convicted

581
00:47:33.642 --> 00:47:35.394
might come back at you someday...

582
00:47:36.144 --> 00:47:38.187
fixate on you
as the cause of their problems.

583
00:47:38.188 --> 00:47:39.565
It's so easy

584
00:47:40.858 --> 00:47:42.901
to build that up in your mind...

585
00:47:44.403 --> 00:47:47.698
until it becomes a reality
that you're afraid to come true.

586
00:47:48.323 --> 00:47:51.243
When Billy Russo escaped.
I didn't have any of those feelings.

587
00:47:53.620 --> 00:47:55.539
And now that's all I can think about.

588
00:47:58.458 --> 00:48:00.334
Is that ridiculous of me?

589
00:48:00.335 --> 00:48:01.420
No.

590
00:48:02.754 --> 00:48:03.755
No.

591
00:48:04.298 --> 00:48:06.341
But he's been gone weeks. so why now?

592
00:48:06.925 --> 00:48:09.302
I treated Billy for a long time.

593
00:48:09.303 --> 00:48:13.180
He had memory loss. blank spots.
both physical and emotional.

594
00:48:13.181 --> 00:48:17.059
You. for instance.
How he came to be injured.

595
00:48:17.060 --> 00:48:20.396
Much of his anger was about not having
answers to those questions.

596
00:48:20.397 --> 00:48:22.149
And I'm afraid that he's gonna...

597
00:48:23.817 --> 00:48:25.485
come back looking for answers.

598
00:48:26.445 --> 00:48:28.071
He's got those answers now.

599
00:48:31.408 --> 00:48:33.076
I don't follow.

600
00:48:34.119 --> 00:48:36.580
Russo was in my apartment. Dr. Dumont.

601
00:48:38.081 --> 00:48:41.292
He came looking for those answers
at the end of a gun.

602
00:48:41.293 --> 00:48:44.170
You saw the news?
The robbery. Frank Castle?

603
00:48:44.171 --> 00:48:46.464
Yes. Billy spoke of Castle often.

604
00:48:46.465 --> 00:48:48.133
Castle is the reason that...

605
00:48:49.217 --> 00:48:50.551
that Billy can't remember.

606
00:48:50.552 --> 00:48:53.262
Castle sounds even worse than Russo.

607
00:48:53.263 --> 00:48:54.556
No.

608
00:48:56.266 --> 00:48:58.310
No. Castle's a whole other thing.

609
00:49:00.646 --> 00:49:03.065
You know what?
The truth is I'm jealous of them both.

610
00:49:04.691 --> 00:49:08.737
Neither of them give a shit.
Absolute purity of purpose.

611
00:49:09.613 --> 00:49:11.156
You know them both well.

612
00:49:11.615 --> 00:49:14.576
Oh. yeah. I've got a real insight.

613
00:49:17.204 --> 00:49:19.373
Maybe if you did. you'd be drinking. too.

614
00:49:21.333 --> 00:49:22.793
I might have some wine.

615
00:49:23.585 --> 00:49:24.670
If you're staying.

616
00:49:26.838 --> 00:49:27.839
Sure.

617
00:49:30.634 --> 00:49:32.552
I've got nowhere else to go anyway.

618
00:49:41.395 --> 00:49:42.688
Well. you took your time.

619
00:49:43.355 --> 00:49:44.648
You got news for me?

620
00:49:47.109 --> 00:49:48.527
You are the news. brother.

621
00:49:51.822 --> 00:49:53.573
How you doin'. Robbie?

622
00:50:02.207 --> 00:50:03.917
Come on. please. Join me.

623
00:50:04.710 --> 00:50:05.794
Have a seat.

624
00:50:16.888 --> 00:50:17.889
Top shelf.

625
00:50:18.473 --> 00:50:21.226
Not like the shit we used to drink.

626
00:50:25.814 --> 00:50:27.899
I know that I wear a suit now. but...

627
00:50:29.192 --> 00:50:31.111
do me the respect
of having a drink with me.

628
00:50:33.280 --> 00:50:34.740
I ain't changed that much.

629
00:50:36.533 --> 00:50:37.617
I have.

630
00:50:38.285 --> 00:50:39.618
That's for sure.

631
00:50:39.619 --> 00:50:41.996
I don't know.
cat got your tongue. or what?

632
00:50:41.997 --> 00:50:44.416
You used to be the loudest...

633
00:50:45.417 --> 00:50:48.295
most garrulous mofo I knew.

634
00:50:49.796 --> 00:50:52.174
Put a couple of these in you.
and you wouldn't shut up.

635
00:50:53.592 --> 00:50:56.136
Always a man for a rousing speech.

636
00:50:57.512 --> 00:50:59.556
The man you knew isn't here.

637
00:51:06.521 --> 00:51:08.690
Now. that's the million-dollar question.
isn't it?

638
00:51:09.983 --> 00:51:11.026
Literally.

639
00:51:13.153 --> 00:51:15.906
The man I knew left 12 years ago
to make a buy.

640
00:51:17.115 --> 00:51:19.618
Disappeared. Along with our money.

641
00:51:20.660 --> 00:51:21.995
Where did he go?

642
00:51:22.829 --> 00:51:24.122
The truth?

643
00:51:25.749 --> 00:51:28.001
The alternator on my truck went bad.

644
00:51:30.420 --> 00:51:31.545
Twelve years bad?

645
00:51:31.546 --> 00:51:34.549
Yeah. well. long enough
to get me in trouble at a bar...

646
00:51:35.383 --> 00:51:38.178
with a man who didn't like my tattoos
or my politics.

647
00:51:39.971 --> 00:51:42.099
Cost him his life and nearly mine.

648
00:51:45.060 --> 00:51:48.188
Staring at the floor of a jail cell...

649
00:51:50.315 --> 00:51:51.691
I thought my life was done.

650
00:51:52.359 --> 00:51:54.152
But then God sent a man

651
00:51:55.028 --> 00:51:57.155
that showed me it wasn't a coincidence.

652
00:51:58.031 --> 00:51:59.491
my breaking down there.

653
00:52:00.158 --> 00:52:01.743
I wasn't lost.

654
00:52:02.410 --> 00:52:03.620
I was found.

655
00:52:07.207 --> 00:52:10.042
Danny. He was just a kid when you left.

656
00:52:10.043 --> 00:52:13.088
Fourteen years old. Just a punk kid.

657
00:52:14.714 --> 00:52:17.174
Running messages and errands
around the clubhouse.

658
00:52:17.175 --> 00:52:19.136
You probably never looked at him twice.

659
00:52:20.303 --> 00:52:21.763
But he looked up to you.

660
00:52:22.556 --> 00:52:24.432
You were everything he wanted to be.

661
00:52:25.684 --> 00:52:28.353
Hell on wheels with no qualms
and no conscience.

662
00:52:29.855 --> 00:52:31.773
A true believer in what we stood for.

663
00:52:36.444 --> 00:52:37.946
We all thought that.

664
00:52:40.615 --> 00:52:42.409
You were a god.

665
00:52:43.702 --> 00:52:44.703
No.

666
00:52:45.954 --> 00:52:47.330
I was a sinner.

667
00:52:48.582 --> 00:52:50.208
But I've been born again.

668
00:52:51.126 --> 00:52:54.045
And now I'm with the people
who will inherit the earth.

669
00:52:55.839 --> 00:52:56.840
Yeah.

670
00:52:57.549 --> 00:52:58.758
Six feet of it.

671
00:53:01.887 --> 00:53:03.513
You know the price for betrayal.

672
00:53:05.223 --> 00:53:06.600
You know how this has to go down.

673
00:53:10.645 --> 00:53:12.105
To be redeemed...

674
00:53:13.481 --> 00:53:15.358
you gotta pay for your sins in full.

675
00:53:28.330 --> 00:53:29.622
I...

676
00:53:29.623 --> 00:53:31.082
I don't know how you do it.

677
00:53:32.042 --> 00:53:34.084
I literally just shot somebody.

678
00:53:34.085 --> 00:53:37.631
and the way that I feel right now.
I don't think that I'll ever do it again.

679
00:53:38.423 --> 00:53:42.469
I mean. I just keep seeing
how scared he was. you know? Like...

680
00:53:43.887 --> 00:53:46.556
Yeah. He got what he needed.

681
00:53:48.225 --> 00:53:49.976
- Seriously?
- Yup.

682
00:53:50.769 --> 00:53:53.230
Yeah. you're right.
You know. you are different.

683
00:53:58.151 --> 00:53:59.319
But I know you...

684
00:54:00.278 --> 00:54:02.280
I know you hated pulling that trigger.

685
00:54:03.031 --> 00:54:04.115
But you did it.

686
00:54:05.075 --> 00:54:06.284
That kept you alive.

687
00:54:07.786 --> 00:54:08.787
Yeah.

688
00:54:10.121 --> 00:54:11.748
But is that all there is now?

689
00:54:12.916 --> 00:54:14.251
That's it? It's just...

690
00:54:15.085 --> 00:54:16.336
alive or dead?

691
00:54:17.170 --> 00:54:18.713
Them or us?

692
00:54:20.090 --> 00:54:21.174
Yeah. I'm...

693
00:54:22.217 --> 00:54:25.303
I'm gonna do whatever I can
to make that different for you.

694
00:54:27.222 --> 00:54:30.934
I just... I gotta deal with Bill.
and I'm gonna finish those Schultzes.

695
00:54:34.729 --> 00:54:37.399
You're gonna go and do
whatever it is that you want to do.

696
00:54:42.404 --> 00:54:43.862
What if Billy kills you?

697
00:54:43.863 --> 00:54:44.990
Nah.

698
00:54:46.533 --> 00:54:49.828
No. I'm not the one that dies. kid.

699
00:54:51.746 --> 00:54:53.498
I'm the one that does the killing.

700
00:54:56.543 --> 00:54:58.919
The thing is. every time
I try to be someone different.

701
00:54:58.920 --> 00:55:00.797
that's when the wrong people get hurt.

702
00:55:09.389 --> 00:55:12.309
This is such a total flustercluck.

703
00:55:13.768 --> 00:55:16.187
Shit.

704
00:55:17.814 --> 00:55:19.274
"Flustercluck."

705
00:55:26.573 --> 00:55:28.074
Yes. it is. kid.

706
00:55:32.495 --> 00:55:33.663
Yes. it is.
